591
00:42:47,109 --> 00:42:48,170
[SPEAKER_18]: Hello, Mr. Graham.

592
00:42:48,230 --> 00:42:50,211
[SPEAKER_18]: Nice to see, nice to hear your voice.

593
00:42:50,251 --> 00:42:53,173
[SPEAKER_18]: Thank you guys so much for your time.

594
00:42:53,213 --> 00:42:53,954
[SPEAKER_18]: I appreciate it.

595
00:42:53,974 --> 00:42:59,197
[SPEAKER_16]: Have a wonderful event as usual.

596
00:42:59,837 --> 00:43:00,658
[SPEAKER_18]: Yes, thank you.

597
00:43:00,678 --> 00:43:01,158
[SPEAKER_18]: We will.

598
00:43:01,238 --> 00:43:02,379
[SPEAKER_18]: I hope you'll all join us.

599
00:43:03,099 --> 00:43:06,181
[SPEAKER_16]: We'll all come down just to say hello and spend some money.

600
00:43:06,201 --> 00:43:09,103
[SPEAKER_18]: That's always a good thing.

601
00:43:09,123 --> 00:43:10,144
[SPEAKER_18]: All right.

602
00:43:10,204 --> 00:43:11,125
[SPEAKER_18]: Have a good night, everyone.

603
00:43:11,165 --> 00:43:11,725
[SPEAKER_18]: Thank you so much.

604
00:43:12,317 --> 00:43:12,917
[SPEAKER_16]: I know.

605
00:43:16,259 --> 00:43:17,859
[SPEAKER_16]: Well, we got Boston Ski and Sports.

606
00:43:18,099 --> 00:43:19,900
[SPEAKER_16]: Kevin, next.

607
00:43:25,742 --> 00:43:28,223
[SPEAKER_07]: Is Kevin still there?

608
00:43:29,463 --> 00:43:30,324
[SPEAKER_05]: Yeah, he's taking notes.

609
00:43:31,724 --> 00:43:35,246
[SPEAKER_07]: Whose mom is on the phone?

610
00:43:45,283 --> 00:43:46,404
[SPEAKER_16]: Oh, Chris.

611
00:43:47,504 --> 00:43:49,465
[SPEAKER_16]: I didn't realize I was on mute.

612
00:43:49,825 --> 00:43:50,746
[SPEAKER_16]: Told on yourself.

613
00:43:51,266 --> 00:43:52,807
[SPEAKER_16]: He muted.

614
00:43:56,308 --> 00:43:58,429
[SPEAKER_16]: So Boston Ski and Sports is next?

615
00:43:59,310 --> 00:44:04,172
[SPEAKER_11]: Yeah, Reggie, I don't think- Mark's not on the call?

616
00:44:04,192 --> 00:44:08,894
[SPEAKER_11]: Not on the call right now, but let me just scroll down to the request.

617
00:44:09,855 --> 00:44:13,917
[SPEAKER_11]: I did talk to Mark before the last meeting.

618
00:44:15,524 --> 00:44:23,988
[SPEAKER_11]: And he did say that he's not planning on using Tufts for the spring, so this is actually a reduction than what he has in the past.

619
00:44:24,608 --> 00:44:31,151
[SPEAKER_11]: But as we said, it'll be on Tuesday and Thursday nights at Memorial Field in South Parkfield.

620
00:44:35,173 --> 00:44:38,775
[SPEAKER_21]: Do we know if Medford High JV, are they using Tufts?

621
00:44:40,756 --> 00:44:41,616
[SPEAKER_11]: Yes, JV is.

622
00:44:42,236 --> 00:44:43,877
[SPEAKER_21]: Oh, then there's no conflict really.

623
00:44:45,948 --> 00:44:49,651
[SPEAKER_16]: So hub didn't come back last year, did they?

624
00:44:49,671 --> 00:44:55,276
[SPEAKER_11]: They came back in the fall, right?

625
00:44:56,697 --> 00:44:59,720
[SPEAKER_11]: Could be right, if you give me one minute I can actually look it up on the calendar.

626
00:45:07,506 --> 00:45:09,848
[SPEAKER_16]: I think that would be the only conflict that we would have.

627
00:45:17,698 --> 00:45:27,802
[SPEAKER_11]: So May, Volo Sports was using it on Wednesdays and Thursday nights from seven to 10.

628
00:45:28,042 --> 00:45:29,523
[SPEAKER_16]: And then- Who was it?

629
00:45:31,204 --> 00:45:31,524
[SPEAKER_11]: Volo?

630
00:45:31,544 --> 00:45:31,924
[SPEAKER_11]: Who was it?

631
00:45:32,704 --> 00:45:33,165
[SPEAKER_16]: Who was it?

632
00:45:37,486 --> 00:45:41,328
[SPEAKER_11]: I'm sorry, I still didn't- It's Volo, V-O-L-O.

633
00:45:43,429 --> 00:45:44,889
[SPEAKER_16]: They were using it for softball?

634
00:45:45,510 --> 00:45:46,090
[SPEAKER_11]: Softball, yeah.

635
00:45:49,967 --> 00:45:55,230
[SPEAKER_16]: Well, Boston Ski and Sports has used Memorial before, right?

636
00:45:56,630 --> 00:45:57,251
[SPEAKER_16]: Yes, they used to.

637
00:45:57,271 --> 00:45:58,331
[SPEAKER_16]: Over the years, they've used.

638
00:45:58,732 --> 00:46:01,733
[SPEAKER_16]: So do you think, do we think that Volo's coming back?

639
00:46:02,834 --> 00:46:08,877
[SPEAKER_11]: I don't have a request in, but I believe last year they had some concerns with field conditions.

640
00:46:10,097 --> 00:46:10,778
[SPEAKER_16]: At Memorial?

641
00:46:11,978 --> 00:46:12,199
[SPEAKER_11]: Yes.

642
00:46:14,140 --> 00:46:15,560
[SPEAKER_16]: So they may or may not come back.

643
00:46:17,581 --> 00:46:18,842
[SPEAKER_11]: Yeah, I haven't heard from them.

644
00:46:19,282 --> 00:46:22,965
[SPEAKER_11]: but I remember last year they had concerns about field positions.

645
00:46:24,206 --> 00:46:25,266
[SPEAKER_16]: How come we didn't hear about it?

646
00:46:26,227 --> 00:46:27,028
[SPEAKER_11]: You didn't hear about it.

647
00:46:27,048 --> 00:46:28,889
[SPEAKER_11]: I think you actually were the point on it.

648
00:46:29,490 --> 00:46:32,112
[SPEAKER_16]: Oh, Jesus.

649
00:46:32,672 --> 00:46:33,993
[SPEAKER_16]: The mind is a terrible thing.

650
00:46:34,013 --> 00:46:40,798
[SPEAKER_11]: You're the one who told me that they had concerns about the fields.

651
00:46:41,478 --> 00:46:41,859
[SPEAKER_16]: Oh, okay.

652
00:46:43,620 --> 00:46:47,463
[SPEAKER_11]: But again, I haven't received any requests for follow-up.

653
00:46:48,378 --> 00:46:54,501
[SPEAKER_16]: So if necessary, the only conflict would be the Thursday night and we can probably move them around, right?

654
00:46:54,661 --> 00:46:56,381
[SPEAKER_16]: We could probably move Volo around.

655
00:46:57,582 --> 00:46:57,782
[SPEAKER_11]: Yeah.

656
00:46:58,542 --> 00:46:59,223
[SPEAKER_11]: Yeah, I don't know.

657
00:46:59,243 --> 00:47:02,044
[SPEAKER_11]: Can you see the calendar on the share view or do I have to reshare?

658
00:47:02,604 --> 00:47:03,184
[SPEAKER_16]: No, it's there.

659
00:47:04,145 --> 00:47:04,365
[SPEAKER_11]: Yeah.

660
00:47:05,625 --> 00:47:07,706
[SPEAKER_11]: So, I mean, you can see it.

661
00:47:07,846 --> 00:47:08,647
[SPEAKER_16]: It's real tiny.

662
00:47:10,007 --> 00:47:10,187
Yeah.

663
00:47:11,968 --> 00:47:12,468
[SPEAKER_10]: Is that better?

664
00:47:13,248 --> 00:47:13,909
[SPEAKER_16]: Yeah, that's better.

665
00:47:14,889 --> 00:47:16,150
[SPEAKER_16]: Now I got to put on my other glasses.

666
00:47:18,438 --> 00:47:19,279
[SPEAKER_16]: I can't read the words.

667
00:47:21,882 --> 00:47:23,725
[SPEAKER_16]: OK, so Volos on Thursday nights.

668
00:47:26,628 --> 00:47:28,851
[SPEAKER_16]: And Boston skiing sports was on.

669
00:47:30,313 --> 00:47:30,994
[SPEAKER_16]: Tuesday nights.

670
00:47:31,815 --> 00:47:35,079
[SPEAKER_21]: I mean, if they wanted the field, they would have put in a request.

671
00:47:35,199 --> 00:47:36,601
[SPEAKER_21]: It's kind of a snooze you lose.

672
00:47:39,593 --> 00:47:46,475
[SPEAKER_16]: True, true, but we'd like to have our returners, you know, get as much as exposure as they possibly can.

673
00:47:46,595 --> 00:47:51,636
[SPEAKER_16]: So I think that you're right, that they should have come back, come to us sooner.

674
00:47:51,696 --> 00:47:53,076
[SPEAKER_16]: Maybe they don't want to come to us.

675
00:47:55,437 --> 00:47:55,837
[SPEAKER_16]: I don't know.

676
00:47:56,197 --> 00:47:58,358
[SPEAKER_16]: I think we should just go with Boston Ski and Sports.

677
00:47:58,478 --> 00:48:01,058
[SPEAKER_16]: Boston Ski and Sports has been with us for 20 something years.

678
00:48:01,598 --> 00:48:05,199
