[SPEAKER_11]: Mark usually has, so.

688
00:48:49,375 --> 00:48:49,635
[SPEAKER_16]: All right.

689
00:48:49,655 --> 00:48:51,277
[SPEAKER_16]: So we, we have an option for them.

690
00:48:51,777 --> 00:48:51,997
[SPEAKER_09]: Yeah.

691
00:48:52,037 --> 00:48:53,418
[SPEAKER_09]: I say we can get both on top.

692
00:48:53,438 --> 00:48:55,160
[SPEAKER_16]: Okay.

693
00:48:55,320 --> 00:49:00,324
[SPEAKER_16]: If they come, if they come, is everybody in agreement with this?

694
00:49:01,185 --> 00:49:01,645
[SPEAKER_16]: Yes.

695
00:49:01,665 --> 00:49:02,285
[SPEAKER_07]: Yes.

696
00:49:02,946 --> 00:49:03,166
[SPEAKER_07]: Yes.

697
00:49:04,407 --> 00:49:04,627
[SPEAKER_16]: Yes.

698
00:49:04,667 --> 00:49:04,847
[SPEAKER_16]: Yes.

699
00:49:05,228 --> 00:49:05,468
[SPEAKER_07]: Yes.

700
00:49:05,988 --> 00:49:06,168
[SPEAKER_07]: Yes.

701
00:49:09,602 --> 00:49:10,202
[SPEAKER_16]: That's a yes.

702
00:49:13,785 --> 00:49:15,146
[SPEAKER_16]: On to Method Youth Soccer.

703
00:49:17,247 --> 00:49:17,967
[SPEAKER_14]: Good evening, sir.

704
00:49:17,987 --> 00:49:19,468
[SPEAKER_14]: How are you doing?

705
00:49:20,309 --> 00:49:21,149
[SPEAKER_14]: I'm doing great.

706
00:49:22,090 --> 00:49:24,992
[SPEAKER_14]: And thank you, Colleen, for the shout out about all the kids playing.

707
00:49:26,153 --> 00:49:29,595
[SPEAKER_14]: I am happy to tell you we could break 800 this season.

708
00:49:30,055 --> 00:49:30,355
[SPEAKER_10]: Wow.

709
00:49:30,375 --> 00:49:31,056
[SPEAKER_10]: That's awesome.

710
00:49:32,297 --> 00:49:35,078
[SPEAKER_10]: That's great.

711
00:49:35,098 --> 00:49:37,100
[SPEAKER_14]: We're also going to be, there was some discussion,

712
00:49:38,012 --> 00:49:41,013
[SPEAKER_14]: last year about signage honoring Tom Hines.

713
00:49:41,693 --> 00:49:44,933
[SPEAKER_14]: I'm happy to tell you guys, April 1st will be the dedication.

714
00:49:45,373 --> 00:49:49,594
[SPEAKER_14]: The sign is being painted and stained as we speak.

715
00:49:49,834 --> 00:49:55,715
[SPEAKER_14]: And we've already gotten the mayor's blessing and the DPW is involved in installing it.

716
00:49:55,775 --> 00:49:59,636
[SPEAKER_14]: So if anybody's around, we believe it's gonna be a 6 p.m.

717
00:50:00,016 --> 00:50:01,436
[SPEAKER_14]: Saturday, the 1st of April.

718
00:50:02,116 --> 00:50:04,357
[SPEAKER_14]: That's when we're gonna unload it and show it to the world.

719
00:50:04,377 --> 00:50:07,077
[SPEAKER_16]: Are they gonna stick it in concrete?

720
00:50:09,418 --> 00:50:10,159
[SPEAKER_14]: I believe they are.

721
00:50:10,339 --> 00:50:24,925
[SPEAKER_14]: It's a mahogany sign on granite, left and right granite stabilizers into the ground on the corner of Playstead and Century Street Extension at a 45 degree angle.

722
00:50:24,945 --> 00:50:26,446
[SPEAKER_14]: So you'll see it as you approach the park.

723
00:50:28,987 --> 00:50:30,508
[SPEAKER_16]: Wonderful, wonderful.

724
00:50:30,788 --> 00:50:31,728
[SPEAKER_14]: It's a beautiful sign.

725
00:50:31,768 --> 00:50:38,051
[SPEAKER_14]: Mike Marr, who is a local contractor, lives up on the hillside, is a Medford youth soccer coach and parent.

726
00:50:38,650 --> 00:50:46,312
[SPEAKER_14]: Uh, he's the one that's building it and, uh, I get updates and, uh, each update is a little bit more, uh, spine tingling than the one before.

727
00:50:46,332 --> 00:50:48,933
[SPEAKER_14]: So I can't wait for this thing to be unveiled.

728
00:50:49,613 --> 00:50:49,833
[SPEAKER_16]: Good.

729
00:50:50,433 --> 00:50:50,833
[SPEAKER_16]: Wonderful.

730
00:50:51,833 --> 00:50:52,253
[SPEAKER_16]: Wonderful.

731
00:50:53,154 --> 00:50:57,595
[SPEAKER_16]: So, um, it looks like you have the same schedule that you had last year.

732
00:50:57,615 --> 00:51:02,696
[SPEAKER_14]: Uh, I asked for a little bit more time because we have more teams with 800 children.

733
00:51:02,776 --> 00:51:03,396
[SPEAKER_14]: We've got over 450 traveling.

734
00:51:06,858 --> 00:51:10,779
[SPEAKER_14]: And believe it or not, we are setting records with our 3-4 group.

735
00:51:11,499 --> 00:51:19,441
[SPEAKER_14]: We are going to have nine boys teams and seven girls teams, I think is the final count.

736
00:51:19,881 --> 00:51:25,343
[SPEAKER_14]: So there's 16 3-4s that need to play on any given Saturday.

737
00:51:27,283 --> 00:51:33,364
[SPEAKER_14]: So we asked to extend, we probably won't need all the time and we're certainly not gonna schedule a 9 a.m.

738
00:51:33,504 --> 00:51:33,845
[SPEAKER_14]: and a 4.30 p.m.

739
00:51:33,885 --> 00:51:34,045
[SPEAKER_14]: game.

740
00:51:36,040 --> 00:51:40,024
[SPEAKER_14]: because the referees would be staying on the field to do consecutive games.

741
00:51:40,884 --> 00:51:53,236
[SPEAKER_14]: So, you know, we'll, I just want to be able to have that ability in case we have to, because you know, the first day it's going to snow like eight feet and then we'll have to push that game off again like it did last year.

742
00:51:53,256 --> 00:51:54,517
[SPEAKER_16]: Mr. Taylor, please.

743
00:51:56,243 --> 00:51:57,403
[SPEAKER_16]: Do not jinx us.

744
00:51:57,623 --> 00:51:58,524
[SPEAKER_14]: Do not jinx us.

745
00:51:58,924 --> 00:51:59,504
[SPEAKER_21]: We don't say that.

746
00:51:59,805 --> 00:52:02,146
[SPEAKER_21]: We don't say that S word in the parks commission meetings.

747
00:52:02,626 --> 00:52:04,807
[SPEAKER_14]: If you remember last April, our first game.

748
00:52:04,827 --> 00:52:06,328
[SPEAKER_16]: No, we don't remember last April.

749
00:52:06,408 --> 00:52:07,449
[SPEAKER_14]: I can't remember last week.

750
00:52:07,929 --> 00:52:08,890
[SPEAKER_14]: Had to be postponed.

751
00:52:08,930 --> 00:52:11,111
[SPEAKER_14]: Kevin shut that thing down faster than you know what.

752
00:52:11,731 --> 00:52:12,492
[SPEAKER_14]: Yeah.

753
00:52:15,553 --> 00:52:19,636
[SPEAKER_16]: Listen, I don't have any problems except that I don't really want to start March 15th.

754
00:52:21,937 --> 00:52:22,197
[SPEAKER_14]: Okay.

755
00:52:22,277 --> 00:52:23,898
[SPEAKER_14]: Just when do you want to start?

756
00:52:25,432 --> 00:52:32,215
[SPEAKER_16]: I'd really like to check with DPW to find out, I mean, cause I remember they closed one of the fields late last year.

757
00:52:32,816 --> 00:52:33,936
[SPEAKER_16]: Yeah.

758
00:52:34,637 --> 00:52:38,218
[SPEAKER_05]: Mike always likes to have the soccer fields ready to go.

759
00:52:38,318 --> 00:52:40,619
[SPEAKER_05]: So we need his blessing before we go any further.

760
00:52:40,799 --> 00:52:44,581
[SPEAKER_05]: And we've always done that just to make sure that he's got everything in place.

761
00:52:46,062 --> 00:52:50,284
[SPEAKER_14]: We're speaking directly with them as far as lying it up and such.

762
00:52:51,004 --> 00:52:52,285
[SPEAKER_14]: I'm not married to the 15th.

763
00:52:53,297 --> 00:52:58,538
[SPEAKER_14]: We, our first game should be the weekend of the 8th of April.

764
00:52:58,558 --> 00:53:01,939
[SPEAKER_14]: And we generally like to have two weeks warmup.

765
00:53:02,659 --> 00:53:04,800
[SPEAKER_14]: So that would put us like the last week of March.

766
00:53:06,920 --> 00:53:08,321
[SPEAKER_16]: So why don't we do this?

767
00:53:08,381 --> 00:53:13,882
[SPEAKER_16]: Why don't we, why don't we say that I don't have my calendar.

768
00:53:13,922 --> 00:53:14,942
[SPEAKER_16]: Oh, I do have my calendar.

769
00:53:15,062 --> 00:53:15,522
[SPEAKER_16]: Look at that.

770
00:53:18,383 --> 00:53:20,183
[SPEAKER_16]: Last week of March would be the 27th, the 26th.

771
00:53:20,243 --> 00:53:20,383
[SPEAKER_16]: Yeah.

772
00:53:24,628 --> 00:53:25,548
[SPEAKER_14]: So.

773
00:53:27,529 --> 00:53:28,950
[SPEAKER_14]: And that would not be Saturdays.

774
00:53:28,970 --> 00:53:29,950
[SPEAKER_14]: That would just be during the week.

775
00:53:30,910 --> 00:53:32,491
[SPEAKER_14]: We wouldn't need Saturdays until the 8th.

776
00:53:35,012 --> 00:53:40,794
[SPEAKER_14]: Or ideally, the first that we can set up the soccer fields for the sign dedication, right?

777
00:53:42,054 --> 00:53:43,735
[SPEAKER_16]: So what I see for one?

778
00:53:45,675 --> 00:53:50,297
[SPEAKER_14]: So for one for Saturdays going forward, and then if we get out the week before that.

779
00:53:51,658 --> 00:53:52,918
[SPEAKER_14]: Just to start our practices.

780
00:53:55,290 --> 00:53:55,991
[SPEAKER_14]: Okay.

781
00:53:56,091 --> 00:54:01,493
[SPEAKER_14]: I don't necessarily need lined fields, but again, we're in, we're in touch with the, with the guy who runs the robot.

782
00:54:02,053 --> 00:54:02,653
[SPEAKER_14]: Yeah.

783
00:54:02,733 --> 00:54:04,234
[SPEAKER_14]: We got real friendly with him last year.

784
00:54:04,294 --> 00:54:07,215
[SPEAKER_14]: So we're going to make sure we maintain that relationship.

785
00:54:09,176 --> 00:54:11,737
[SPEAKER_16]: Well, so, so we're looking at the 27th.

786
00:54:11,777 --> 00:54:13,518
[SPEAKER_16]: Yeah, that's fine.

787
00:54:14,578 --> 00:54:14,858
[SPEAKER_16]: All right.

788
00:54:15,438 --> 00:54:15,799
[SPEAKER_16]: Yeah.

789
00:54:16,059 --> 00:54:18,079
[SPEAKER_16]: That, that, that, that works a lot better for us.

790
00:54:18,180 --> 00:54:23,882
[SPEAKER_16]: And I'm pretty sure the DPW, if there's, if there's any questions about that, we can

791
00:54:25,542 --> 00:54:28,143
[SPEAKER_16]: you know, uh, we'll figure out a workaround.

792
00:54:28,764 --> 00:54:31,265
[SPEAKER_14]: We never had a problem with them before.

793
00:54:31,325 --> 00:54:35,346
[SPEAKER_14]: We have no problem helping, you know, going both directions here, whatever they need.

794
00:54:35,386 --> 00:54:39,208
[SPEAKER_16]: We'll be happy to help out with any of the commissioners have any other questions?

795
00:54:41,049 --> 00:54:46,511
[SPEAKER_05]: The only thing with the nets, can we get those locked up more and more?

